The paper discusses the design and analysis of locking protocols for resource management in real-time systems, which is a topic related to operating systems (cs.OS) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The use of spin locks to protect shared resources also relates to data structures (cs.DS) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the analysis of blocking time and its impact on task finishing time involves the study of algorithms and complexity (cs.LO).
